            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> But I also already follow a cwd=project-root model and don't know all the reasons why people might have a cwd!=project-root setup\n\nIt's common in web projects to keep backend and frontend in the same repository. For example, in a JavaScript/TypeScript based project:\n\n```\nproject/  <- cwd\n├── apps\n│   ├── backend   <- project root\n│   │   ├── package.json  <- root marker\n│   │   └── …\n│   └── frontend  <- project root\n│       ├── package.json  <- root marker\n│       └── …\n└── …\n```\n",
            "created_at": "2026-02-26T16:13:06Z",
